# Page Headers

Always use `<PageHeader>` from `@/components/page-header` for page titles. Never write raw `<h1>` tags.

```tsx
import { PageHeader, PrimaryLinkButton, PrimaryButton } from '@/components/page-header';

// List page with "New" action
<PageHeader
  title="Strategies"
  subtitle="Multi-step workflows that chain generations together."
  actions={<PrimaryLinkButton href="/strategies/new" icon>New Strategy</PrimaryLinkButton>}
/>

// Detail/edit page with back link
<PageHeader
  backHref={`/strategies/${id}`}
  backLabel={`Back to ${name}`}
  title="Edit Strategy"
/>

// Create/edit form page — title="" hides the h1, save button in actions
<PageHeader
  backHref="/input-presets"
  backLabel="Back to Input Presets"
  title="New Input Preset"
  actions={
    <PrimaryButton onClick={handleCreate} disabled={!canCreate} loading={creating}>
      Create Input Preset
    </PrimaryButton>
  }
/>
```

- `title` renders as `h1 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900`
- `subtitle` accepts `React.ReactNode` — use JSX for rich subtitles with links
- `backLabel` defaults to "Back" when omitted
- `actions` slot goes on the right side of the header row
- Use `PrimaryLinkButton` for navigation CTAs; pass `icon` for a plus icon
- Use `PrimaryButton` for form submit buttons (`onClick`, `disabled`, `loading`)
